-- ETB Shareholders Approve Proposal to Borrow Up to $600 Million
-- B y   C h r i s t i n e   J e n k i n s
-- 2012-05-09T17:50:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-08/etb-shareholders-will-consider-borrowing-up-to-600-million.html
Empresa de Telecomunicaciones de
Bogota SA won shareholder approval of a proposal to take on as
much as $600 million in debt, the phone company serving
 Colombia ’s capital said today in a filing with regulators.  Saul Kattan, ETB’s president, said the funds would be used
for the company’s fiber optic expansion and TV business,
reported  La Republica , a daily. The company would begin
providing cable television in the capital city by the end of the
year, Kattan said, according to La Republica.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Christine Jenkins in  New York  at 
 cjenkins28@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
